								</h2>
								<p class="card-text">
									The children's internal motives and
									expectations, as well as their assessments
									of costs and rewards, were the primary
									causes driving them to the streets.
									Regardless, Although many service providers
									sympathized with street children, many saw
									them as deviants, delinquents, future
									criminals, and a public nuisance. For
									example, service providers tended to
									recommend safe havens and vocational
									schools. their upkeep
								</p>
								<a
