								/></a>
							</div>
							<div class="col-lg-6">
								<h2 class="card-title">
									Why Not Help Where We Can?
								</h2>
								<p class="card-text">
									For the homeless in South Africa, life on
									the streets is a regular daily battle.
									According to Naidoo (2010:131), street
									homeless people were found living on the
									streets, in public restrooms, or under
									bridges because they lacked a permanent
									residence. The homeless on the streets have
									a difficult time storing their stuff, even
									food. For the homeless on the streets,
									finding food and a place to sleep is a
									continual struggle (Thexton 2014:6). As a
									result, some homeless people on the street
									shuffle their things from place to place in
									search of work, food, or a place to stay.
								</p>
								<a
									class="btn btn-primary"
									href="https://www.un.org/development/desa/dspd/wp-content/uploads/sites/22/2019/05/OBIOHA_Emeka_Paper-1.pdf"
									>Read More</a
								>
							</div>
